communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Jaun Cardillo case log
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I would like to respectfully request a log detailing all cases handled by Senior Deputy Medical Examiner Juan Cardillo during his tenure at the Los Angeles County Medical Examiner’s office. The log should include the case numbers, decedent names, and the dates of birth for all decedents listed. Thank you for your attention to this matter.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Cassie Sipe

communications.communication:

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Julie Kellerman Case log
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

On June 1, 2016, former supervisor Julie Kellerman was arrested and terminated for driving under the influence while on duty. In the interest of transparency, I respectfully request a log of every case she supervised during her tenure as the supervisor of the Medical Examiner’s office. Please include the case number, decedent’s name, date of birth, and the date of birth of all individuals listed in the log.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Cassie Sipe
